---
// src/pages/faq.astro
import AboutLayout from '../layouts/AboutLayout.astro';
---

<AboutLayout
  title="LifeLoggerz Q&A"
  description="Common questions about why I track my life, how my systems work, and how you can adapt them for yourself."
  pubDate="2025-10-20"
  wide={true}
  showViews={false}
  heroImage="/images_webp/faq-movie.webp"
>
  <div class="faq">
    <p>
      This page explains how <strong>LifeLoggerz</strong> works in practice.
      If you want the full background story, check the <a href="/about">About</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2>🚀 Getting Started</h2>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Who is LifeLoggerz for?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            It is for people who want to understand how they spend their time
            and make better decisions from it. Students, researchers, builders,
            or anyone trying to be more intentional with their days.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What should I track first if I’m just starting out?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Start small. Track three things that actually matter to you.
            Usually sleep, work or study time, and one habit you care about.
            Stay consistent before adding more.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How long does logging take each day?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            About five minutes for the basics. Reflection takes longer,
            but that is optional.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What happens if I miss days or fall behind?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            I simplify instead of quitting. Sometimes I fill in basic details later.
            The goal is to stay consistent, not perfect.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <h2>📊 What I Track &amp; Why</h2>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What kinds of things do you track?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            A lot. Sleep, work sessions, habits, health notes, reading,
            movement, social time, and short reflections.
            Some are numbers, some are just notes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you actually review all this data?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            I review trends monthly and yearly. I do not reread everything.
            The value is having a record when I need it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Why do you track so many things?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Small decisions add up. Tracking helps you see patterns
            you would miss otherwise.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <h2>🛠 Tools, Templates &amp; Systems</h2>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do I need coding or Google Sheets experience to use your systems?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            No. Most templates work as they are.
            The automation is optional if you want to go further.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I modify your templates for personal use?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Yes. You can adapt them however you want.
            If you share them publicly, a small credit is appreciated.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Why do you use Google Sheets instead of apps or Notion?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            It is simple and flexible. I can shape it exactly how I want,
            and my data stays fully mine.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you plan to release more templates or tools?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Yes. I am sharing more over time.
            Suggestions help decide what to build next.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <h2>🔒 Privacy, Data &amp; Backups</h2>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you share your real personal data?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            No. I share structure and examples, not real logs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How do you protect and back up your logs?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            I keep cloud and offline backups and export important files.
            If something matters, I treat it like an archive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <h2>🌱 Philosophy &amp; Purpose</h2>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Isn’t this level of tracking excessive?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            It would be if it felt heavy.
            If it ever does, I simplify it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do systems limit creativity, or increase it?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            For me, they increase it.
            Structure clears my head so I can focus on real work.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What’s the difference between efficiency and effectiveness?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            I focus on doing the right things first.
            Then I make them faster.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Are you proactive or reactive?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Mostly proactive. The systems help me stay ahead,
            but they also help me handle things calmly when plans change.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What are you ultimately working toward?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Clarity and discipline.
            The systems are just tools to get there.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <h2>📬 Contact &amp; Collaboration</h2>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How can I contact you?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Email:
            <strong> lifeloggerz.official@gmail.com</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I suggest a template, feature, or collaboration?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Yes. Good ideas often come from people using the system.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>
</AboutLayout>
